10/10 recommend taking your kids to Disneyland during the holidays 🎄🎅🏼 💫 if you’re going this month, here’s some of our favorite things we did: 

1. Christmas Fantasy Parade: it was the highlight of the trip watching the boys face light up when they saw their favorite characters. 

2. It’s a Small World Holiday decorations. The ride is deck out and perfect when you need a minute to sit and chill. 

3. Character breakfast at Story Tellers Cafe (grab the earliest time as it’s usually less busy and gives you more time with characters) 

4. Visit Santa in Grand California hotel and see the festive decorations (they also have carolers perform throughout the evenings) 

5. Get a Mickey Gingerbread Cookie at Market House on Main Street (arguably the best gingerbread cookie…ever)

#disneyland #christmasatdisneyland #disneyland2022 #disneywithkids

This year, my word is LESS. ☁️

I want less “noise,” so that I can focus on the things that truly matter, which you can read all about in today’s blog post (www.theteacherdiva.com).

How to get the 90’s blow out look with jumbo hot rollers:

1. Dry shampoo in roots if this is day 2 (or 3😉)
2. Section hair. I start with middle top layers and roll back. 
3. If your hair creases from the clips, secure clip to the side (vs. how you are supposed to clamp it). I do two clips per roller for my front layers. 
4. Keep rolling in the way you want your curls to fall. I like mine to go under to look like I used a round brush. 
5. Spray texture spray all over. And let it set while you do makeup / get ready. 
6. Remove clips, run fingers through and voila! 

#hotrollers #90shair #loosecurls
